         <OBJECT_CONTRACT ITEM="1">
            <TITLE>
               <P>Request for Information for an Inertia Measurement System</P>
            </TITLE>
            <CPV_MAIN>
               <CPV_CODE CODE="48000000"/>
            </CPV_MAIN>
            <TYPE_CONTRACT CTYPE="SUPPLIES"/>
            <SHORT_DESCR>
               <P>National Grid, as the electricity system operator (ESO) for Great Britain (GB), is looking to investigate the market available technologies for the provision of a system-measured real-time signal of GB’s inertia.</P>
               <P>The current methodology at National Grid, is to continuously forecast an estimate of the total inertia in the power system, up to 36 hours ahead.</P>
            </SHORT_DESCR>
            <NO_LOT_DIVISION/>
            <OBJECT_DESCR ITEM="1">
               <CPV_ADDITIONAL>
                  <CPV_CODE CODE="72000000"/>
               </CPV_ADDITIONAL>
               <n2016:NUTS CODE="00"/>
               <SHORT_DESCR>
                  <P>National Grid, as the electricity system operator (ESO) for Great Britain (GB), is looking to investigate the market available technologies for the provision of a system-measured real-time signal of GB’s inertia.</P>
                  <P>The current methodology at National Grid is to continuously forecast an estimate of the total inertia in the power system, up to 36 hours ahead.</P>
                  <P>Inertia in GB is forecast using two distinct elements: The 1st component is determined by summating all the known inertia from the synchronised generation on the GB transmission system. A 2nd component of inertia is determined for the distribution system (residual inertia), using a constant adjustment factor for the known GB demand. Both inertia components are summated, to determine a value for total GB system inertia.</P>
                  <P>A real-time value of system inertia is later calculated using the same approach, by using actual system conditions.</P>
                  <P>The total GB inertia figure is then used to determine.</P>
                  <P>For the avoidance of doubt this RFI is not being used as a call for competition and therefore will not be used to pre-select a shortlist of vendors. Please refer to the additional information later in this notice regarding accessing the RFI document.</P>
               </SHORT_DESCR>
            </OBJECT_DESCR>
            <DATE_PUBLICATION_NOTICE>2018-01-19</DATE_PUBLICATION_NOTICE>
         </OBJECT_CONTRACT>
